description: The list-style shorthand CSS property and the list-style-image, list-style-position, and list-style-type longhand properties set the position and appearance of a list item's marker.
description_html: The list-style shorthand CSS property and the list-style-image, list-style-position, and list-style-type longhand properties set the position and appearance of a list item's marker.
name: List style

spec.title: CSS Lists and Counters Module Level 3

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 86, this property did not accept an <image> type, and required the URL of an image.

firefox_android.notes: Before Firefox for Android 86, this property did not accept an <image> type, and required the URL of an image.

safari.notes: In Safari, if a block element is the first child of a list element declared as list-style-position: inside, then the marker box is placed on the same line as the block element.

safari_ios.notes: In Safari on iOS, if a block element is the first child of a list element declared as list-style-position: inside, then the marker box is placed on the same line as the block element.

webview_ios.notes: In WebView on iOS, if a block element is the first child of a list element declared as list-style-position: inside, then the marker box is placed on the same line as the block element.

opera.notes: Until version 15, only decimal numbers display.

opera_android.notes: Until version 15, only decimal numbers display.

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 38, Firefox added a dot as suffix of the number for ethiopic-numeric (for example, ፫. instead of ፫). The specification later defined the absence of a suffix, which Firefox 38 followed.

firefox_android.notes: Before Firefox for Android 38, Firefox for Android added a dot as suffix of the number for ethiopic-numeric (for example, ፫. instead of ፫). The specification later defined the absence of a suffix, which Firefox for Android 38 followed.
